<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1874-12-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1874-12-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="284" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d284">
                        <head>No. 576.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Cushing</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Fish</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1874-12-04"><hi rend="italic">December</hi> 4,
                                1874</date>. (Received December 4.)</dateline></opener>
                        <p rend="flushleft"><hi rend="smallcaps">Fish</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Secretary of State, Washington:</hi></p>
                        <p>Long note received from Ulloa at twelve last night, which discusses the
                            legal questions from his point of view, but concedes indemnity to the
                            United States on the same basis as to Great Britain, and also trial of
                            local authorities implicated. Telegram of details in preparation.</p>
                        <closer><signed>CUSHING.</signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>